Courtesy #DStv403 JOHANNESBURG - Kulula and British Airways are back in the air. This comes after the South African Aviation Authority reinstated its air operations certificate following a five-day suspension citing safety concerns. READ | Flight Safety | WATCH | Comair CEO is to blame - Numsa Thousands of passengers were left stranded when flights were suspended and had to seek other alternatives but what's the recourse for those who lost flights through Comair's suspension? Peter Nkuna from The Ombudsman for Short-term Insurance says there's a general sense of relief that Comair is back but beyond the inconvenience, there has been a significant financial loss for many. Passengers can now fly via British Airways and Kulula. eNCA's Heidi Giokos is at OR Tambo Airport monitoring the situation.